                ],
                "institute": "3BULBUL"
              },
              "free_text": [
                " The betatron of the Medical Academy of",
                " Bulgaria with the end-point energy of 43 MeV."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "SAMPLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "A natural indium target was used for the production of",
                " ll0m,gIn,  enriched  to 80-95%  118Sn,  119Sn (purity",
                " 93.5%) and l2lSb (purity 97.5%) for the production of",
                " 117m,gIn. The samples had a cylindrical form as close",
                " as possible to a point source. They were contained in",
                " thin  walled PVC capsules (10 mm in diameter,  0.5 mm",
                " thick) and shielded with a 1 mm thick cadmium foil to",
                " reduce   the  neutron  interactions.  The  capsulated",
                " samples were closed in another  plexiglass  container",
                " with 6 mm thick walls."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "DETECTOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "GELI"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " Different high-resolution Ge(Li)  spectrometers",
                " (FWHM  <  3  keV  at  1.3  MeV) with maximal absolute",
                " photopeak efficiency 3-6%.  For low energy  gamma-ray",
                " measurements a \"thin\" detector was used."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "METHOD": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "ACTIV"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " The induced activity  measurements  were  made",
                " observing the gamma-ray spectra."
              ]
            }
          ],
